meanings.definition: Unable to be suppressed or restrained.
meanings.sent1: Her insuppressible laughter filled the room with joy.
meanings.sent2: The insuppressible excitement of the children on the playground was contagious.
meanings.sent3: His insuppressible urge to dance whenever he heard music always brought smiles to those around him.
meanings.sent4: The insuppressible energy of the puppy was like a whirlwind in the house.
meanings.sent5: The insuppressible colors of the sunset painted the sky in a breathtaking display.

meanings.definition: Not capable of being kept from public knowledge or attention.
meanings.sent1: The insuppressible rumors about the celebrity spread like wildfire.
meanings.sent2: The insuppressible news of the new product launch created a buzz in the market.
meanings.sent3: The insuppressible paparazzi followed the famous actor everywhere he went.
meanings.sent4: The insuppressible spotlight on the talented singer made her a household name overnight.
meanings.sent5: The insuppressible curiosity of the crowd grew as they waited for the announcement.
